# CODEOWNERS — guard the SAFETY MACHINERY so the gates can't be silently removed or weakened.
#
# This is the I-7 "meta-gap" fix from the 2026-06-21 Safety-Stop post-mortem: the deploy gates,
# the seal toolchain, the runtime verifier, and the trust anchor are the things that keep a
# mis-sealed image from ever reaching a visitor. A change to any of them deserves a deliberate,
# reviewed eye. Patterns are repo-root-relative; the LAST matching pattern wins.
#
# NOTE: there is intentionally NO catch-all (`* @owner`) line — that would require code-owner
# review on EVERY file and is needless friction for routine app/OS work. Only the paths below are
# gated. CODEOWNERS auto-requests review from these owners; it is ENFORCED only once branch
# protection on `main` turns on "Require review from Code Owners" (see the deploy hardening notes).

# ── The deploy gates themselves (and this file) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
/.github/workflows/      @humuhumu33
/.github/CODEOWNERS       @humuhumu33

# ── The seal toolchain: defines + verifies "every served byte re-derives to its pinned κ" ─────
/system/tools/reseal.mjs                  @humuhumu33
/system/tools/reseal-drift.mjs            @humuhumu33
/system/tools/holo-anchor-sw.mjs          @humuhumu33
/system/tools/seal-served.mjs             @humuhumu33
/system/tools/install-hooks.mjs           @humuhumu33
/.githooks/                               @humuhumu33

# ── The post-deploy boot witness (proves a cold visitor boots with no Safety-Stop) ────────────
/system/tools/holo-cold-boot-witness.mjs  @humuhumu33

# ── The runtime verifier + the trust anchor / closures it enforces (Law L5) ───────────────────
/system/os/holo-fhs-sw.js        @humuhumu33
/system/os/etc/os-closure.json   @humuhumu33
/system/os/etc/os-served.json    @humuhumu33
